---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { languageRows } from "../../facts";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Languages · Squeezy"
  description="Squeezy first-class language support for graph-backed code navigation and bounded fallback behavior."
  activeDoc="/docs/languages/"
  eyebrow="languages"
  heading="First-class language support feeds graph-backed navigation."
  lead="Squeezy gives these languages the strongest local navigation path. Other languages remain usable through bounded search, file reads, shell commands, and verifier tools, but they do not get the same structured cost-saving behavior."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>First-class graph support</h2>
    <div class="matrix compact-matrix">
      {
        languageRows.map((row) => (
          <article class="matrix-row">
            <h3>{row.name}</h3>
            <p>{row.detail}</p>
            {row.status && <span class="status-pill ok">{row.status}</span>}
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Graph tools</h2>
    <p>Language support feeds the same navigation surface: repo maps, declaration search, definition search, reference search, hierarchy, upstream and downstream flow, symbol context, diff context, and read_slice.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Fallback behavior</h2>
    <p>For files outside first-class language support, Squeezy can still inspect the repository with bounded grep, glob, file reads, shell tools, and verifier commands. The agent should treat those paths as ordinary evidence gathering instead of graph-backed cost optimization.</p>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
